data.title: Audi Staff Serving Treasure Coast
data.meta_description: Meet the friendly and knowledgeable staff at Audi Stuart serving Treasure Coast!
data.text:
In 2013, Devin opened the Murgado Automotive Audi Stuart location, where he assumed the position of General Manager. Since then, the dealership has garnered numerous accolades in the automotive industry, including being named JD Power Dealer of Excellence six consecutive years (Diamond Status) and receiving the prestigious Audi Magna Society award six times, including Magna Elite. Additionally, the dealership has been recognized nationally as one of Automotive News' Best Dealerships to Work for, and has received several other industry dealer of the year awards. Audi Stuart has also been twice ranked as the number one dealership in the entire nation for customer satisfaction. Furthermore, Devin has ensured that the dealership is an active and supportive member of the Martin County community by contributing to education, health, and wellness programs. The dealership's efforts to give back, and perform at a high level, are a testament to the positive culture and work environment that Devin has fostered within his teams.

Kirk is a seasoned automotive professional who hails from the northwestern suburbs of Philadelphia. Having been in the auto industry since he was 16 years old, Kirk has accumulated a wealth of knowledge and experience over the years. He started his career as a car washer and has worked his way up the ranks.

With his extensive background in the automotive industry, Kirk has a thorough understanding of how the business has evolved and what it takes to succeed in this fast-paced and competitive field. He is well-versed in all aspects of the industry, from sales and marketing to customer service.

In addition to his professional accomplishments, Kirk also has a passion for sports and outdoor activities. He is an avid tennis player and enjoys spending time on the court whenever he can. He is also a certified scuba diver through PADI and loves exploring the underwater world. Kirk finds the Florida weather to be the perfect environment for his active lifestyle, and he takes advantage of all the opportunities that the state has to offer.

Ken Dunlap is an accomplished and respected service leader in the automotive industry. With over 30 years of experience, Ken has dedicated his career to providing exceptional service to clients and team members alike. He is known for his passion for delivering quality service and creating a culture of excellence, which has earned him the respect of his team at Audi Stuart and many accolades along the way.

Before entering the automotive industry, Ken proudly served our country in the United States Army, where he developed leadership skills and a commitment to excellence that he brings to his work today. Throughout his career, Ken has demonstrated his ability to inspire and lead others to achieve their best.

Bill is an experienced professional who has spent more than 40 years working in the luxury automobile market. Throughout his career, he has held various roles that have allowed him to gain extensive knowledge and expertise in the industry. He has had the opportunity to work with some of the most prestigious luxury automobile brands in the world such as Audi, Bentley, Porsche, Rolls Royce, and BMW vehicles, and he also has unique experience as a motorsport parts coordinator, working with racing teams to provide them with the parts they need to compete at the highest level.

As our Parts manager, Bill has been responsible for overseeing the entirety of our Parts dept, including inventory management and our team of a wholesale and retail specialists.

Gina Prochilo is a Long Island native who grew up in New York. After completing her studies in Business Management, Gina and her family had the opportunity to travel extensively, living in Japan and England. During this time, Gina pursued her interest in Child Development and earned numerous certificates and degrees in the field. She also took college courses in Psychology while in Japan. In 1997, Gina began her professional career beginning as a receptionist and quickly worked her way up through the ranks of the Accounting Office, eventually becoming a Controller. In her current role as Controller, Gina is responsible for overseeing the accounting office for six Murgado Automotive franchises. Her expertise in dealership accounting, combined with her strong leadership skills, allows her to effectively manage complex financial operations while maintaining a high level of accuracy and efficiency. With her extensive knowledge of the industry and her unwavering commitment to excellence, Gina has become a trusted advisor to the dealerships she serves.
